                "citation-title": "Does unit of account affect willingness to pay? Evidence from metaverse LAND transactions✰",
                "abstracts": "© 2022 Elsevier Inc.LAND is a non-fungible token (NFT) representing virtual real estate ownership in The Sandbox metaverse, a digital world built on the Ethereum blockchain. The open nature of a blockchain-based metaverses like The Sandbox allows users to transact in multiple denominations/currencies. We analyze more than 71,000 transactions and find that when transactions are settled in The Sandbox's native utility token (SAND), users pay 3.4% more compared to ETH (in effective USD prices). There are also evidences that users pay less when transactions are settled in wETH and USD-pegged stablecoins (USDC). Thus, the cryptocurrency/token settlement choice (i.e., unit of account) matters for willingness to pay.",
